Geraldine Brooks (actress) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geraldine_Brooks_(actress) 0 For the author of the same name, see Geraldine Brooks (writer)Geraldine Brooks (born Geraldine Stroock; October 29, 1925 – June 19, 1977) was an American actress whose three-decade career on stage as well as in films and on television was noted with nominations for an Emmy in 1962 and a Tony in 1970. She was married to author Budd Schulberg. For the_author of the_same_name , see Geraldine_Brooks ( writer ) Geraldine_Brooks ( born Geraldine_Stroock ; October_29_,_1925 – June_19_,_1977 ) was an_American_actress whose_three-decade_career on stage as_well_as in films and on television was_noted with nominations for an_Emmy in 1962 and a_Tony in 1970 .
